Sentencas: NiFe2 alloy coating was applied on SUS 430 steel substrate for solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) interconnects via magnetron sputtering technology.
Titulo: Application of sputtered NiFe2 alloy coating for SOFC interconnect steel

Sentencas: The coated steel was exposed for 15 weeks in air at 800 degrees C. SEM/EDS and XRD analysis results indicated that NiFe2O4 spinel layer atop chromia sub-layer was obtained on the coated steel.
Titulo: Application of sputtered NiFe2 alloy coating for SOFC interconnect steel

Sentencas: The top NiFe2O4 spinel layer not only suppressed chromia layer growth, but also exhibited excellent effect on retention of out-migration Cr species.
Titulo: Application of sputtered NiFe2 alloy coating for SOFC interconnect steel

Sentencas: The long term durability of the double-layered scale was demonstrated by the distinct adhesion of the steel/chromia and chromia/spinel interfaces.
Titulo: Application of sputtered NiFe2 alloy coating for SOFC interconnect steel

Sentencas: An area specific resistance (ASR) of 49.25 m Omega cm(2) was achieved for NiFe2 coated steel after 15 weeks exposure.
Titulo: Application of sputtered NiFe2 alloy coating for SOFC interconnect steel

Sentencas: NiFe2O4 spinel thermally developed from sputtered NiFe2 coating is promising for the FSS interconnects application.
Titulo: Application of sputtered NiFe2 alloy coating for SOFC interconnect steel
